column5: [/url]">http://  After many hours of going round in circles up and down due to nasty wave action, GB finally gave a a reward.   A few smaller ones were caught later in the week.
Very nice sir.Your time pays off.Seems the way for a few of us.
nice I hope to get some of them too
Thats a nice fish Erich. Well done.  Now to work on the rest of that lower tanning. LMAO
Hahahaha, have to take the socks off more often I guess
Hahahaha, have to take the socks off more often I guess   Not to worry. My pop has the same tan line. You old fellas.
so the elusive GB King does still exist...very rare
so the elusive GB King does still exist...very rare

Nice king! Lake O makes it almost too easy to get them, it means a lot more to get one on GBay. I took a salmon charter there years ago and all we caught was a bunch of 4-5lb bows.  I have the same socks without socks tan just not quite that dramatic LOL  Pete

I grew up on G-Bay till I was 21.Can be tough at times foresure.My late grandfather was persistent and not many days we would not come back without a whitie,steelhead or laker.Back then the commercial fisherman were slaying them bigtime.Nets right outside the front of our house.1/2 mile out.
Open water king fishing in GBay isn't exactly a slammer.  I'm guessing that's what he was referring to.
